            "en-x-generated": "<p><strong>Do you work with a removal firm or a firm that supplies rubble containers?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most removal firms have an annual permit for temporary placement of traffic signs or intakes on public property.<br />\r\nWe recommend you inquire about this before submitting this application.<br />\r\nIf you are not working with a firm or if the firm you are working with does not hold an annual permit, apply for a parking ban using the procedure below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Application procedure:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Deliver the application form at least 10 days before you wish to place the traffic signs on the public domain.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>by e-mail to <a href=\"mailto:insi@gent.be\">insi@stad.gent</a></li>\r\n\t<li>by post to the service Roads, Bridges and Waterways, department Collections Public Space, Botermarkt 1, 9000 Ghent</li>\r\n\t<li>by delivery to the Buildings Desk</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>When can you expect your decision?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will receive the decision in writing no later than 10 days after receipt of your fully completed application.<br />\r\nYou will be notified in writing if any information is missing. The 10-day period only starts when we have all the data to fully process your application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The processing period for your application is extended by 7 days during the collective closures of the week of the Ghent Festivities and during End of Year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Would you like to apply for an extension?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then use the separate document<strong> </strong>'Extend permit'.<br />\r\nYou can apply for an extension if only the period is changed. This means that all the other details of your permit remain the same.<br />\r\nSend us your renewal application <strong>at least 7 days before the expiry date of your current permit</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Where can you rent traffic signs?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you do not have the necessary traffic signs yourself, you can rent one from a private company.<br />\r\nYou can find companies in the Yellow Pages under the heading 'road and yard signs'.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>When to place the signs?</strong><br />\r\nYou should place the traffic signs on the public domain <strong>at least 48 hours before the start</strong> of the move or works.<br />\r\n<strong>If there is no work on certain days, the signs should be covered </strong>.<br />\r\nAs soon as the works are over, the signs should be removed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Passing on number plates</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When placing no parking signs, you must provide the number plates of the vehicles currently parked there.<br />\r\nYou must immediately <a href=\"https://eforms.gent.be/Productie4.0/formulier/sc_kennisgevingnummerplaten.aspx\">send</a> these number plates, together with the place, date and time, <a href=\"https://eforms.gent.be/Productie4.0/formulier/sc_kennisgevingnummerplaten.aspx\">online</a> to the police.<br />\r\n<strong>Concrete instructions for reporting number plates will be sent to you along with your permit.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If cars are parked between the plates during the licensed period, please contact the Police (101). Only the Police have the authority to look up the details of number plates.<br />\r\n<strong>The Police will act on problems with incorrectly parked cars only if they were notified in good time (i.e. 48 hours in advance).</strong></p>"
